00:33:52,822 --> 00:33:56,284
<i>♪ With a head full of snow ♪</i>

526
00:33:56,368 --> 00:33:59,412
<i>♪ With a head full of snow ♪</i>

527
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:03,667
<i>♪ In the window ♪</i>

528
00:34:04,251 --> 00:34:07,504
<i>♪ There's a face you know ♪</i>

529
00:34:07,587 --> 00:34:11,049
<i>♪ Don't the nights pass slow ♪</i>

530
00:34:11,132 --> 00:34:13,718
<i>♪ Don't the nights pass slow ♪</i>

531
00:34:13,802 --> 00:34:15,303
[muffled] …heretic, right?

532
00:34:15,387 --> 00:34:18,598
Then, fucking Thomas Moron
thinks he knows how to save the world.

533
00:34:18,682 --> 00:34:23,019
So Henry VIII's like,
"All right, then. Rehydrate the masses!"

534
00:34:23,603 --> 00:34:25,730
So we go outside, and I put this biltong--

535
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:29,234
Jack, can… Sorry. Can you shut up a sec?
I need to talk to you about something.

536
00:34:29,985 --> 00:34:32,362
Oh yeah? What's this big news, then?

537
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:33,572
No, no. Don't tell me.

538
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:37,534
After ten years you finally asked Jin out,
now that she's dating an admiral.

539
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:39,578
I have pancreatic cancer.

540
00:34:41,246 --> 00:34:42,289
Stage four.

541
00:34:45,584 --> 00:34:47,002
It's spread all over.

542
00:34:48,587 --> 00:34:50,088
Liver, lungs.

543
00:34:52,841 --> 00:34:54,843
Median survival time is, uh…

544
00:34:54,926 --> 00:34:58,555
It's, like, two to six months, so…

545
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:02,642
There it is.

546
00:35:03,351 --> 00:35:04,352
[quietly] Fuck that.

547
00:35:05,353 --> 00:35:06,229
What?

548
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:09,899
Some NHS doctor says so,
and you're just gonna accept it?

549
00:35:09,983 --> 00:35:10,900
No.

550
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,403
No, no, no. No, no. Fuck that.

551
00:35:13,486 --> 00:35:15,488
We'll… We'll go to Switzerland.

552
00:35:15,572 --> 00:35:19,409
-Or New York, or somewhere fucking good.
-No, Jack. I'm too far gone, mate.

553
00:35:20,702 --> 00:35:23,538
All they can do now is
to make me comfortable. All right?

554
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:25,874
So they're gonna operate
on my tumors, that's…

555
00:35:25,957 --> 00:35:29,711
They're gonna… fluff the pillows
on the sinking ship.

556
00:35:29,794 --> 00:35:31,212
And I said,

557
00:35:32,589 --> 00:35:33,882
"Fuck that, pal."

558
00:35:35,634 --> 00:35:37,969
-My money says they're wrong.
-Come on, Jack.

559
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:39,596
You fucking come on.

560
00:35:41,598 --> 00:35:44,851
This is what you always do, man.
You-- You give up on everything--

561
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:46,019
I didn't give up--

562
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:48,313
You quit physics,
thought you weren't smart enough.

563
00:35:48,396 --> 00:35:51,107
You gave up on Jin because
you thought you were punching above.

564
00:35:53,526 --> 00:35:57,030
You're not giving up
on your own fucking life. [sniffles]

565
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:01,660
Fuck that.

566
00:36:07,791 --> 00:36:08,625
Eat.

567
00:36:08,708 --> 00:36:09,751
[sighs]

568
00:36:10,460 --> 00:36:14,005
-I don't feel like eating, Jack.
-Will. Just…

569
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,009
Try.

570
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:27,852
[tense music playing]

571
00:36:33,066 --> 00:36:35,944
[ominous orchestral music playing]

572
00:37:04,764 --> 00:37:08,727
[Count] If I may, Emperor Zhou,
the sun is Yang.

573
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,813
The night is Yin.

574
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:17,193
Presently we are caught
in the chaos of imbalance.

575
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:20,530
But we shall be no longer.

576
00:37:20,613 --> 00:37:22,907
I bring you salvation
for our civilization--

577
00:37:22,991 --> 00:37:24,743
[Zhou] Yes. Yes, get on with it.

578
00:37:25,285 --> 00:37:28,079
I have created a code for the universe.

579
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:31,458
And with this code,
I can predict the movements of the sun.

580
00:37:32,041 --> 00:37:33,752
That's what they all say.

581
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:41,968
[tense, rhythmic music playing]

582
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:50,685
I hope your prediction can save us,
for your sake.

583
00:37:50,769 --> 00:37:53,271
-This is prophecy, not prediction.
-[Zhou] What?

584
00:37:54,147 --> 00:37:56,691
Speak aloud, child, or die.

585
00:37:56,775 --> 00:37:57,692
[clears throat]

586
00:38:01,613 --> 00:38:04,783
Emperor. This is the <i>I Ching.</i>

587
00:38:05,325 --> 00:38:07,952
It's beautiful, but it's not scientific.

588
00:38:08,036 --> 00:38:08,912
Explain.

589
00:38:08,995 --> 00:38:10,789
[Jin] I don't think
it will solve your problem.

590
00:38:10,872 --> 00:38:13,583
It's divination.
It doesn't follow any physical laws.

591
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:16,586
Physical laws?

592
00:38:16,669 --> 00:38:18,546
Yeah. The laws of physics.

593
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:23,134
Everything we've observed
to be true about the world.

594
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:26,179
Which world?

595
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:28,681
[Count] Your Imperial Majesty.

596
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:34,646
The code is complete.
It will answer your questions.

597
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:35,605
[Zhou] Very well.

598
00:38:36,189 --> 00:38:38,983
When will it be safe
to rehydrate the masses?

599
00:38:42,195 --> 00:38:44,197
[sizzling]

600
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:59,087
The chaotic era
will last another eight days.

601
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:04,801
And when it is over, we will enjoy
a glorious stable era for 63 years

602
00:39:05,385 --> 00:39:09,138
with a climate so mild,
it will be a golden age.

603
00:39:09,222 --> 00:39:10,849
Sky. Now.

604
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:17,647
Let the days fly past.

605
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:24,237
Let the days fly past.

606
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:25,530
[Jin] Hmm?

607
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:28,783
Put your hand on the ground.
It speeds up time.

608
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,830
[dramatic orchestral music playing]

609
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:34,873
[Jin gasps]

610
00:39:55,852 --> 00:39:57,061
There!

611
00:39:57,145 --> 00:39:59,647
Stability for 63 years.

612
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:02,191
-Is it possible?
-It is, Emperor.

613
00:40:03,985 --> 00:40:07,196
I advise you to awaken your dynasty
and let it prosper.

614
00:40:08,907 --> 00:40:11,534
Rehydrate!

615
00:40:47,028 --> 00:40:49,030
[bright instrumental music playing]

616
00:41:20,645 --> 00:41:22,647
[group exclaims]

617
00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:33,032
[laughing]

618
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:45,044
[Jin inhales sharply]

619
00:41:50,258 --> 00:41:52,301
[uplifting orchestral music playing]

620
00:41:53,678 --> 00:41:55,096
[Follower gasps]

621
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:56,180
[exhales]

622
00:42:02,311 --> 00:42:03,855
You didn't abandon me.

623
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:05,231
Of course not.

624
00:42:14,032 --> 00:42:16,034
[wind picks up]

625
00:42:18,828 --> 00:42:19,871
[Jin gasps]

626
00:42:20,455 --> 00:42:22,582
Count! Look!

627
00:42:23,499 --> 00:42:25,418
[Zhou] No.

628
00:42:27,462 --> 00:42:29,922
[ominous string music playing]

629
00:42:32,258 --> 00:42:34,260
[wind gusting]

630
00:42:44,145 --> 00:42:46,147
[all screaming]

631
00:42:50,359 --> 00:42:51,652
[Follower] Copernicus!

632
00:42:52,195 --> 00:42:53,863
Copernicus, please!

633
00:42:53,946 --> 00:42:55,490
[wind whistling]

634
00:42:55,573 --> 00:42:57,617
[crowd clamoring]

635
00:42:57,700 --> 00:42:59,118
[Follower] Save me!

636
00:43:03,331 --> 00:43:06,000
-[gasps]
-[Follower] Copernicus, please!

637
00:43:06,542 --> 00:43:07,668
[Jin groans]

638
00:43:10,296 --> 00:43:12,131
[Follower] Please, Copernicus!

639
00:43:12,215 --> 00:43:14,592
[Jin grunting]

640
00:43:16,469 --> 00:43:18,012
[Follower] Copernicus!

641
00:43:18,096 --> 00:43:20,473
[people shouting]

642
00:43:21,390 --> 00:43:22,475
[Follower] Save me!

643
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:26,938
Please!

644
00:43:28,231 --> 00:43:29,941
Save me!

645
00:43:32,193 --> 00:43:34,654
-[Jin grunts]
-[icy shards splintering]

646
00:43:44,664 --> 00:43:46,666
[frigid wind whipping]

647
00:43:46,749 --> 00:43:48,751
[Jin breathing shakily]

648
00:43:55,466 --> 00:43:57,468
[wind dies down]

649
00:44:10,231 --> 00:44:11,315
[Jin sighs]

650
00:44:13,151 --> 00:44:15,153
[somber instrumental music playing]

651
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:25,580
Civilization number 137
was obliterated by extreme cold.

652
00:44:26,789 --> 00:44:28,332
You did not save them.

653
00:44:28,833 --> 00:44:33,004
But you did establish the superiority
of science over mysticism.

654
00:44:33,754 --> 00:44:38,217
In level two, you must use science
to save the next civilization.

655
00:44:40,261 --> 00:44:41,637
[Jin gasps]

656
00:44:41,721 --> 00:44:44,807
[stirring orchestral music playing]

657
00:45:03,951 --> 00:45:06,787
[music fades slowly]

658
00:45:06,871 --> 00:45:10,625
-[birds calling]
-[horn honking in distance]

659
00:45:21,177 --> 00:45:22,553
[door opens]

660
00:45:39,779 --> 00:45:42,198
I received a complaint about you,
Clarence.

661
00:45:42,281 --> 00:45:43,699
What did I do now?

662
00:45:43,783 --> 00:45:45,826
Apparently you've been smoking
in your office.

663
00:45:47,078 --> 00:45:49,956
Yeah, I'd go outside, but it's a long way.

664
00:45:53,084 --> 00:45:54,293
I'll go outside next time.

665
00:45:54,377 --> 00:45:57,255
No need. I sacked the guy
who made the complaint.

666
00:45:57,838 --> 00:46:01,092
If he's worrying about you,
he's not worrying about our adversaries.

667
00:46:01,175 --> 00:46:02,843
Well, I wish you hadn't fired him.

668
00:46:03,469 --> 00:46:04,762
Tell me about Evans.

669
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:07,223
[Clarence sighs]

670
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:10,101
Turns out he likes paying for things.

671
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:14,063
Anti-vax propaganda,
5G conspiracy theories,

672
00:46:14,146 --> 00:46:16,774
anti-science politicians around the world.

673
00:46:17,566 --> 00:46:20,361
I'd bet money
he's behind all the rest of it too.

674
00:46:20,861 --> 00:46:23,531
What about the stars?
Did he pay for them to disappear?

675
00:46:23,614 --> 00:46:26,617
There's someone behind everything.
You just have to dig.

676
00:46:27,159 --> 00:46:29,662
Well, I dug up this.

677
00:46:31,372 --> 00:46:35,084
I was reading up on radio telescopes
after the stars blinked.

678
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:41,173
Back in 1977, Ohio State University
detected a 72-second sequence.

679
00:46:41,966 --> 00:46:44,093
They called it the Wow! signal

680
00:46:44,176 --> 00:46:47,763
because it made
all the astrophysicists go, "Wow!"

681
00:46:47,847 --> 00:46:50,641
They said it looked like
an attempt at communication.

682
00:46:50,725 --> 00:46:52,101
Attempt from who?

683
00:46:52,810 --> 00:46:54,270
Little green men.

684
00:46:55,813 --> 00:46:56,772
What's it say?

685
00:46:56,856 --> 00:46:58,065
No one knows.

686
00:46:58,149 --> 00:47:00,192
No one's been able to decode it,

687
00:47:00,276 --> 00:47:03,154
and nobody outside of Ohio State
detected it.

688
00:47:06,407 --> 00:47:09,327
Except for one observatory
in Northeast China.

689
00:47:10,953 --> 00:47:11,954
And?

690
00:47:13,164 --> 00:47:15,041
Well, it's probably nothing.

691
00:47:15,124 --> 00:47:16,208
[sniffles]

692
00:47:17,126 --> 00:47:18,210
[sighs]

693
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,797
Funny thing about Mike Evans.

694
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:26,969
Guess where he lived in 1977?

695
00:47:27,970 --> 00:47:29,972
[birds singing]

696
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:32,058
[gentle orchestral music playing]

697
00:48:27,822 --> 00:48:29,657
[man, in Mandarin] No coffee,

698
00:48:29,865 --> 00:48:31,742
sorry.

699
00:48:32,910 --> 00:48:33,828
No coffee,

700
00:48:34,161 --> 00:48:35,913
many years.

701
00:48:40,709 --> 00:48:43,712
[in English] May I ask why you are here?

702
00:48:46,465 --> 00:48:48,426
I'm trying to save lives.

703
00:48:48,509 --> 00:48:49,635
The locals?

704
00:48:49,718 --> 00:48:51,846
-[scoffs]
-[Ye Wenjie] How are you helping--

705
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:54,098
You hear "lives,"
and you think human lives.

706
00:48:54,181 --> 00:48:56,559
Of course,
we always think of ourselves first.

707
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:05,234
I'm trying to save a bird, a subspecies
of the northwestern brown swallow.

708
00:49:05,317 --> 00:49:08,904
I doubt I'll succeed. The loggers,
they work faster than one person can.

709
00:49:08,988 --> 00:49:11,323
You planted all those trees yourself?

710
00:49:11,407 --> 00:49:12,825
Mm-hmm.

711
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:17,204
How long will you stay here?

712
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:19,748
My whole life if I have to.

713
00:49:22,501 --> 00:49:25,171
How many people
get the chance to save a species?

714
00:49:25,838 --> 00:49:30,509
Ten thousand species go extinct
every year because of the greed of one.

715
00:49:33,387 --> 00:49:35,473
May I ask why <i>you </i>are here?

716
00:49:37,183 --> 00:49:41,395
We are looking for a site
to build a radio astronomy laboratory.

717
00:49:41,479 --> 00:49:42,313
Here?

718
00:49:43,189 --> 00:49:45,941
-This land isn't yours.
-It shouldn't belong to anyone.

719
00:49:46,025 --> 00:49:47,443
It belongs to the People.

720
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:49,320
And the People will destroy it.

721
00:49:49,403 --> 00:49:52,490
Ruin an entire ecosystem for a radio lab.

722
00:49:53,032 --> 00:49:54,408
It doesn't trouble you?

723
00:49:56,452 --> 00:49:58,204
The stupidity of the People?

724
00:50:01,957 --> 00:50:03,209
It isn't up to me.

725
00:50:10,841 --> 00:50:12,134
I have work to do.

726
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:14,678
[in Mandarin] What did he say?

727
00:50:14,762 --> 00:50:16,305
He understands.

728
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:18,557
[in English] Yes, I understand. Please go.

729
00:50:32,530 --> 00:50:34,532
[tense music playing]

730
00:50:36,909 --> 00:50:40,412
[in English] "In nature,
nothing exists alone."

731
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:57,680
What's your name?

732
00:50:57,763 --> 00:50:58,764
Ye Wenjie.

733
00:51:00,474 --> 00:51:01,475
Mike Evans.

734
00:51:05,938 --> 00:51:08,107
-I will try to stop them.
-[Evans sighs]

735
00:51:16,282 --> 00:51:18,576
[in Mandarin] Ye Wenjie,
we have discussed it,

736
00:51:18,659 --> 00:51:19,660
Commissar Lei and I…

737
00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:22,329
Site 1 fits all the parameters.

738
00:51:22,413 --> 00:51:23,455
Minimal electromagnetic interference, 

739
00:51:23,539 --> 00:51:24,498
access to good roads for construction--

740
00:51:24,582 --> 00:51:26,166
That's true of Site 2 as well.

741
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:28,043
The villagers at Site 2--

742
00:51:28,127 --> 00:51:29,878
Are desperate for work.

743
00:51:29,962 --> 00:51:31,505
Too desperate.

744
00:51:31,589 --> 00:51:34,800
They'll see the lab
as a piece of meat to take bites from.

745
00:51:35,676 --> 00:51:39,013
Commissar Lei and I have decided,
together, that Site 2 is better.

746
00:51:39,513 --> 00:51:40,598
[Ye Wenjie sighs]

747
00:51:40,681 --> 00:51:43,100
I know you're disappointed.

748
00:51:44,476 --> 00:51:48,856
You're sure it's not because
you're trying to help the American?

749
00:51:48,939 --> 00:51:53,861
You've been doing good work
for eight years. Don't throw it away.

750
00:51:57,323 --> 00:51:59,158
There is something I can do for you.

751
00:52:00,284 --> 00:52:03,120
The Commissar gave me
the names and records

752
00:52:03,203 --> 00:52:05,414
of the new arrivals
at the work camp in Qiqihar.

753
00:52:05,497 --> 00:52:07,916
In case there's anyone
who could be useful for us.

754
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:13,130
No scientists, unfortunately.
But there's a woman called Tang Hongjing.

755
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:15,633
She used to be a Red Guard.

756
00:52:15,716 --> 00:52:19,845
During a struggle session
at Tsinghua University in 1966,

757
00:52:19,928 --> 00:52:22,848
she dealt a fatal blow to a professor

758
00:52:24,475 --> 00:52:26,310
called Ye Zhetai.

759
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:49,500
[official speaking Mandarin]

760
00:53:16,402 --> 00:53:20,406
This is a new era. The past is finished.

761
00:53:20,489 --> 00:53:23,200
The past is not finished.

762
00:53:23,283 --> 00:53:25,911
You want me to repent?

763
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:27,996
You don't think you should?

764
00:53:28,080 --> 00:53:30,457
Then who will repent for me?

765
00:53:30,541 --> 00:53:33,502
Who will atone for what I have lost?

766
00:53:34,128 --> 00:53:38,298
The Party sent me to Shaanxi
to work the wheat fields.

767
00:53:38,382 --> 00:53:40,175
After a day's work,

768
00:53:40,259 --> 00:53:42,720
I didn't even have the energy
to wash my clothes.

769
00:53:42,803 --> 00:53:47,307
We slept on the ground at night.
Listening to the sound of wolves.

770
00:53:47,391 --> 00:53:52,438
My arm was infected with gangrene.

771
00:53:52,521 --> 00:53:55,274
The guards pinned me down…

772
00:53:57,443 --> 00:54:00,446
and cut it off me.

773
00:54:04,700 --> 00:54:05,826
[crying softly]

774
00:54:05,909 --> 00:54:08,704
I was just a kid.

775
00:54:09,455 --> 00:54:15,127
I was just a kid when I watched you

776
00:54:17,087 --> 00:54:21,967
break my father's skull with a belt.

777
00:54:23,886 --> 00:54:26,889
They told me you're clever.

778
00:54:27,181 --> 00:54:29,516
And you should be.

779
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:32,603
Daughter of an academic.

780
00:54:32,811 --> 00:54:35,022
I was not clever.

781
00:54:35,481 --> 00:54:38,275
I had no utility.

782
00:54:38,358 --> 00:54:41,278
Your mind spared you.

